## Coverage

Enforce in both CI and local dev:

```bash
# Local
pytest --cov=src/arvel --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=80

# CI
pytest --cov --cov-context=test --cov-report=xml
coverage combine && coverage report --fail-under=80
```

Branch coverage is enabled via `[tool.coverage.run] branch = true`.

---

## CI Test Splitting

```bash
# Fast (no services, < 30 seconds)
pytest -m "not db and not integration" --timeout=10

# DB only (SQLite, no external services)
pytest -m "db and not pg_only and not integration"

# Full integration (all services, CI only)
pytest -v --cov
```

---

## Checklist (Before Merging Test Changes)

- [ ] Tests pass locally: `pytest tests/ -v`
- [ ] No new warnings with `filterwarnings = ["error"]`
- [ ] Coverage doesn't drop: `pytest --cov --cov-fail-under=80`
- [ ] Appropriate markers applied (`@pytest.mark.db`, etc.)
- [ ] No test ordering dependencies
- [ ] DB tests use transaction rollback
- [ ] Fakes for unit tests; real drivers for integration tests
- [ ] Test names follow `test_<what>_<condition>_<expected>`
- [ ] Parametrize uses named `id=` parameters
- [ ] No `os.environ` mutation — use `monkeypatch`
- [ ] No broad `pytest.raises(Exception)`
- [ ] HTTP tests assert status + body + headers
